-- ============================================================================
-- Notes
-- ============================================================================
--
-- Key principles from RLM paper:
-- 1. Decomposition: Break long inputs into snippets via grammars
-- 2. Recursion: Process each snippet independently
-- 3. Aggregation: Combine results in a principled way
-- 4. Programmability: LLM controls decomposition via prompts
--
-- Benefits:
-- - Handles inputs 100x beyond context window
-- - Better quality than full-context (less distraction)
-- - Cheaper per query (smaller prompts)
-- - More interpretable (clear decomposition)
--
-- FMPL advantages:
-- - Grammars are first-class (powerful decomposition)
-- - Streams are immutable (safe recursion/branching)
-- - Cursors enable observation without copying
-- - Pattern matching unifies parsing and control flow
